16/09/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi said Wednesday (15 September) that next year would be a challenge both for Kosovo and the international community. After meeting with the chairman of the Council of Europe, Norwegian Foreign Minister Jan Petersen, Rexhepi said that in 2005 the international community should formulate a single stance on the future of the province. Petersen agreed, but stressed the need for implementation of standards in Kosovo. 
In other news Wednesday, international prosecutors announced that they have indicted two ethnic Albanians for the June murder of a Serb teenager. Dimitrije Popovic, 17, was shot in the head by a gunman in a passing car. (Tanjug, Beta, B92, AFP - 15/09/04) 
